India after Gandhi: The History of the World's Largest Democracy is a book by Indian historian Ramachandra Guha, published by HarperCollins in August 2007. A history of the Indian nation after it gained independence from the British Empire on 15 August 1947, India after Gandhi was chosen Book of the Year by The Economist, The Wall Street Journal and Outlook, among others. The book won the 2011 Sahitya Akademi Award for English.Guha's magnum opus India After Gandhi was later translated in Hindi in two volumes, "Bharat Gandhi Ke Baad" and "Bharat Nehru Ke Baad", by Sushant Jha, an alumuni of Indian Institute of Mass Communication, New Delhi.